race.description: Ladbrokes Owners Promotion QTIS Maiden Handicap
race.comment: NEXT STOP JUPITER (4) is a progressive filly who was third on debut and then finished fourth, just a length behind the winner last time out over 1400m at Townsville. Blinkers go on for the first time, and she is the one to beat here. HERE'S MASON (10) was well supported but failed to fire last time out. He drops 4.5kg and can bounce back. Include in all combinations. MISSISSIPPI DREAM (5) ran well for a placing two starts back at Townsville but was below her best last time, finishing sixth over 1500m at Rockhampton. She drops 200m and is worth another chance. MR SUGAR DADDY (3) improved nicely last start, finishing third and only half a length from the winner over 1400m at Townsville 8 days ago. This race suits, and he's a strong top 4 chance here. READY AND BETTA (6) hit the line strongly when two lengths off at Rockhampton last time out, finishing third. Stick with him for all top 4 combos.
